        <characteristic name="Type" typeId="077c342f-d7b9-45c6-b8af-88e97cafd3a2">Assault 4</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="S" typeId="59b1-319e-ec13-d466">4</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="AP" typeId="75aa-a838-b675-6484">0</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="D" typeId="ae8a-3137-d65b-4ca7">1</characteristic>
        <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="837d-5e63-aeb7-1410">Flames, Poison(4+)</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Pest Explosion" typeId="72c5eafc-75bf-4ed9-b425-78009f1efe82" typeName="Abilities" hidden="false" id="4cbc-f60b-666f-444a">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="21befb24-fc85-4f52-a745-64b2e48f8228">If the model is destroyed, it always explodes. The explosion range is 6&quot;.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Putrescent Fog" typeId="72c5eafc-75bf-4ed9-b425-78009f1efe82" typeName="Abilities" hidden="false" id="89cc-b4d2-2fa7-e2bc">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="21befb24-fc85-4f52-a745-64b2e48f8228">At the start of each activation, the model can create a Putrescent Fog with a &quot;Stand &amp; Shoot&quot; command. To do so, place a Putrescent Fog marker (a 3&quot; radius circle) within 7&quot; of any friendly unit bearing the Mark of Nurgle. All enemy units treat the zone as difficult terrain and must take one Toughness test per model if they touch or move over the circle during their activation. For each failed test, the unit suffers an automatic Wound loss with no save allowed.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Additional Armor" typeId="57f5-93cf-6d5d-4dca" typeName="Vehicle_Equipment" hidden="false" id="3edb-dd3c-a9a4-4923">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model ignores the first temporary vehicle damage each round.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Demonic Possession" typeId="57f5-93cf-6d5d-4dca" typeName="Vehicle_Equipment" hidden="false" id="584d-3531-ab72-88df">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">- The model gains the &quot;Daemon&quot; ability (Note: a 5+ invulnerability save).
- The model reduces its BS and WS values by -1.
- The model ignores temporary vehicle damage.
- If the model is transporting a unit, during each activation of the unit roll 1D6 per model. On a roll of 1 and 2 the unit suffers one Mortal Wound.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Hunter-killer Missile" typeId="57f5-93cf-6d5d-4dca" typeName="Vehicle_Equipment" hidden="false" id="8db6-57e0-af0e-40f0">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model may shoot once per game a Hunter-killer missile with this profile: Range 120&quot;, Heavy 1, Strength 8, AP -3, Damage 2, AT(1).</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Daemonic Resilience" typeId="57f5-93cf-6d5d-4dca" typeName="Vehicle_Equipment" hidden="false" id="1fdb-f463-73ea-2322">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The first &quot;Engine damage&quot; or &quot;Weapon destroyed&quot; effect is ignored, whichever occurs first.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Improved Targeting" typeId="57f5-93cf-6d5d-4dca" typeName="Vehicle_Equipment" hidden="false" id="e4a5-8410-427c-f4d6">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model does not have to declare its ranged weapon targets before firing and can choose a new target for each weapon.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Jammer" typeId="57f5-93cf-6d5d-4dca" typeName="Vehicle_Equipment" hidden="false" id="a49b-b5d3-4e99-3ff2">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">Equipment such as icons or homing beacons do not function within 6&quot; of the model. Additionally, units arriving via deepstrike that land within 12&quot; roll 4D6 instead of 2D6 for scattering.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
    <profile name="Smoke Launcher" typeId="57f5-93cf-6d5d-4dca" typeName="Vehicle_Equipment" hidden="false" id="ed6f-eb64-cf0e-d7a6">
      <characteristics>
        <characteristic name="Description" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model can use its Smoke Launcher once per game:
- During normal activation, instead of firing weapons.
- If it has not yet carried out its order this round and is targeted by an enemy unit.
Enemy units can only deal glancing hits with ranged attacks until the next activation.</characteristic>
      </characteristics>
    </profile>
