  <sharedRules>
    <rule name="Summoning" id="39d0-d291-fcff-36db" hidden="false">
      <description>If the army contains any units from the &quot;&quot;Chaos Daemons&quot;&quot; codex, these units must start the game in reserve, with the exception of Nurglings who can be deployed regularly.
Character models are not allowed to join a unit from the Chaos Daemons codex.
Chaos Daemons can not be used to fulfil mandatory AOP selections.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Not Mandatory HQ" id="36c9-3534-db35-edcb" hidden="false">
      <description>Can not be the mandatory HQ selection.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Plaguehost" id="7afc-4029-fddb-77fe" hidden="false">
      <description>- The army got access to all units from this codex that can take the Mark of Nurgle and all units must take it.
- The army got access to all units from the &quot;&quot;Chaos Demons&quot;&quot; codex with the Mark of Nurgle.
- The army got access to all entries from the Armory.
- Plague Marines can be taken as Troops.
- Only models that already come equipped with the Mark of Nurgle count towards the 25% limitation for Troops.
- Legionnaires can not be taken at all.
- Frag grenades for all models are exchanged with Blight grenades at no additional cost.
- Vehicles must upgrade Combi-bolters for +2 points each to gain &quot;&quot;Poison(4+)&quot;&quot;, Combi-flamers to Combi-plague belcher for +2 points each and Combi-melta for +2 points each to gain &quot;&quot;Poison(4+)&quot;&quot; on the bolter part .
- No other &quot;&quot;Units&quot;&quot; or &quot;&quot;Traits&quot;&quot; may be selected.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Weapons of Another Age" id="23a6-911a-f4d4-8eb1" hidden="false">
      <description>The army has access to Horus Heresy Space Marine units, weapons, and equipment. All models must have the Mark of Nurgle.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Nurgle&apos;s Sacred 7" id="8fdc-8699-27bc-fbe5" hidden="false">
      <description>If the unit consists of 7, 14 or 21 models at the start of the game, the squad leader gets an additional attack and the &quot;Personal Icon&quot; equipment.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Mark of Slaanesh" id="1577-5bee-8914-6750" hidden="false">
      <description>The model gains +1 Initiative.
A character model or Monstrous Creature additionally gains additionally +2&quot; Movement.
Vehicles lower the Ld or close combat result of hostile models by -1 within a 18&quot; range and by -2 within 9&quot;.
Counts as a veteran ability.
If a unit has a Mark, its effects are already included in the profile.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Mark of Khorne" id="29a3-29ca-26dd-95b6" hidden="false">
      <description>The model gains +1 Attack
A character model or Monstrous Creature gains additionally +1 Strength.
Vehicles cause double hits when performing a Tank Shock.
Counts as a veteran ability.
If a unit has a Mark, its effects are already included in the profile.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Mark of Nurgle" id="bc6a-3f9c-5861-3f87" hidden="false">
      <description>The model gets +1T. 
A character model or Monstrous Creature gains additionally +1W. 
Vehicles may roll 2D6 during each Reinforcement phase. 
On a roll of 7+ they may remove one temporary damage result or one permanent damage result or restore one lost HP.
Counts as a veteran ability.
If a unit has a Mark, its effects are already included in the profile.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Mark of Tzeentch" id="3932-3917-7aea-d44e" hidden="false">
      <description>The model gains the &quot;Warded&quot; ability.
A character model or Monstrous Creature becomes a psyker and knows 1 power from any discipline.
If the model is already a psyker, instead it can manifest and deny an additional power per turn.
Vehicles get a Warpflamer weapon (Range: 9&quot;, Type: Assault 4, S: 4, AP: -1, Dmg: 1, Flames).
Counts as a veteran ability.
If a unit has a Mark, its effects are already included in the profile.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Favoured Units" id="fcf0-cba2-536b-fa4d" hidden="false">
      <description>If a unit has a Mark of Chaos and starts the game with a number of models equal to the deity&apos;s sacred number (or a multiple thereof), it counts as favored. 
Squad leaders receive +1 attack and a personal icon. Squad leaders are single models within a unit that have sole access to the armory. 
The sacred numbers are as follow: 9 for Tzeentch, 8 for Khorne, 7 for Nurgle and 6 for Slaanesh.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Mark of Chaos Undivided" id="c48e-8a4a-d584-3829" hidden="false">
      <description>The first time this model kills an enemy unit, it receives the benefits of one Mark of Chaos like a non-character model.
If it kills a second unit, it gains the additional benefit like a character model would.
After the third kill it receives one Daemon weapon ability from the chosen god.
After the fourth kill the models base stats are replaced by those of a Daemon Prince of the chosen god.
If the model loses its last Wound before getting at least one Mark of Chaos benefit, it is replaced with a Chaos Spawn under the control of the opposing player.
If a unit has a Mark, its effects are already included in the profile.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Animosity of the Gods" id="fc39-3a40-cc1c-6c06" hidden="false">
      <description>When creating your army list, choose your most expensive HQ model. Its Mark of Chaos determines which marks and/or units may be used. A model with a Mark of Chaos may only join units with the same mark or none at all.


See rulebook for full chart.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Legacy of the Arch Traitor" id="7a1a-1920-b95d-f893" hidden="false">
      <description>The army has access to the Word Bearers Armory.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Legacy of the Hydra" id="fe8a-26eb-ab2f-f4f1" hidden="false">
      <description>The army has access to the Alpha Legion Armory.
Can only select units with no Mark or the Mark of Chaos Undivided.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Legacy of the Iron Lord" id="c918-3d6d-bec4-6e60" hidden="false">
      <description>The army has access to the Iron Warriors Armory.
Can only select units with no Mark or the Mark of Chaos Undivided.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Legacy of the Night Haunter" id="175b-4cb2-a658-f9ef" hidden="false">
      <description>The army has access to the Night Lords Armory.
Can only select units with no Mark or the Mark of Chaos Undivided.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Legacy of the Warmaster" id="7188-829b-26dd-e458" hidden="false">
      <description>The army has access to the Black Legion Armory.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Unpredictable Mutations" id="9a29-47b8-f19e-f462" hidden="false">
      <description>Models with this ability cannot use transport vehicles. At the start of each activation, this unit may return 1D3 dead models to the game.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Bodyguard (Chaos Ogryn only)" id="55c3-91fa-3c41-7c0f" hidden="false">
      <description>Wounds inflicted must first be allocated to the model before other models in the unit can be selected. Attacks with the “Precision” rule take a -1 hit penalty if they affect an attached character.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Master of Possesion" id="2f8d-1028-72a8-c16f" hidden="false">
      <description>You may roll 1D6 or 2D6 on the &quot;Daemonic corruption&quot; table.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Daemonic Corruption" id="b806-6ea9-44b9-3576" hidden="false">
      <description>Daemonic corruption: Roll 2D6 at the start of the activation if this model is accompanied by a unit and set up on the battlefield (being in a transporter does not count towards being on the battlefield for that purpose). Apply following results to that unit permanently:


-1: +2&quot; Movement
-2: +1 Strength
-3: +1 Toughness
-4: +1 Initiative
-5: +1 Wound
-6: +1 Attack


If a result is applied for the third time, the unit is destroyed. Place a chaos spawn for every fourth wound (rounded down) within 3&quot; of the model with this ability.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
